Stenoma ortholampra is a moth in the family Depressariidae. It was described by Edward Meyrick in 1930. It is found in Brazil.The wingspan is about 35 mm. The forewings are lilac brown, towards the costa except at the apex becoming darker brown, with the costa dark brown. There is a slightly curved linear dark brown mark on the end of the cell and a nearly straight dark brown subterminal line, as well as some ochreous tinge towards the apical edge. The hindwings are ochreous orange.